quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  78,31,"Indeed the place of success is for the pious."
  78,32,"Gardens and grapes."
  78,33,"And maidens of a single age."
  78,34,"And an overflowing cup."
  78,35,"In which they shall neither hear lewd talk, nor any lie."
  78,36,"A reward from your Lord – a grossly sufficient bestowal."
  78,37,"Lord of the heavens and the earth, and all whatever is between them – the Most Gracious – with Whom no one will have the right to talk."
  78,38,"The day when Jibreel and all the angels will stand in rows; none will be able to speak except one whom the Most Gracious commands and who spoke rightly. (Prophet Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him – will be the first to be granted permission to intercede.)"
  78,39,"That is the True Day; therefore whoever wills may take the path towards his Lord."
  78,40,"We warn you of a punishment that has come near; a day on which man will see what his own hands have sent ahead, and the disbeliever will say, “Alas – if only I were dust!”"
  79,1,"By oath of those who harshly pull out the soul. (Of the disbeliever)"
  79,2,"And who softly release the soul. (Of the believer)"
  79,3,"And who glide with ease."
  79,4,"And who quickly present themselves."
  79,5,"And who plan the implementation."
  79,6,"On the day when the trembling one will tremble. (The disbelievers will certainly taste the punishment.)"
  79,7,"And the following event will come after it."
  79,8,"Many a heart will flutter on that day!"
  79,9,"Unable to lift their gaze."
  79,10,"The disbelievers say, “Will we really return to our former state?”"
  79,11,"“When we have become decayed bones?”"
  79,12,"They said, “So this return is an obvious loss!”"
  79,13,"So that is not but a single shout."
  79,14,"So they will immediately be in an open plain."
  79,15,"Did the news of Moosa reach you?"
